race.comment: PORSHA CRYSTAL (9) was a winner two back then tested at Sandown Hillside and not disgraced when midfield. Back in grade and will be camped just off the leading division. Can atone. CHERRABAH (15) is a lightly raced mare having had just two runs. Started only once last campaign when she got off the mark with an effortless maiden win but may well have had an issue as she wasn't seen again. Has big upside and certainly wouldn't shock. The stablemate is scratched. MACEDONIAN MARVEL (1) is another resuming from a long break. Has ability and returns here after a string of trials and hit-outs. Should run well on best figures. SHOWMARA (5) is a lightly raced galloper resuming. Was tested in tougher grade and out to 2000m last time in. Fitter for two trials and off the inside should be getting the gun run. Will wind up late.
